1
00:00:11,600 --> 00:00:13,600
Where were you when
I was at the hospital?

2
00:00:13,667 --> 00:00:15,733
I took care of Danilo,
my husband.

3
00:00:15,800 --> 00:00:18,500
Or did you take care
of my daughter?

4
00:00:18,567 --> 00:00:19,733
Why would I do that?

5
00:00:19,800 --> 00:00:22,367
Whatever Madam Olive wants
to do with her daughter

6
00:00:22,433 --> 00:00:23,700
is none of your business.

7
00:00:23,767 --> 00:00:26,167
I don't want to think
ill of your mom.

8
00:00:26,233 --> 00:00:29,200
But doesn't she purposely
make you sick?

9
00:00:29,267 --> 00:00:31,100
- Mommy!
- Ma'am!

10
00:00:31,167 --> 00:00:32,133
Ma'am! Please stop!

11
00:00:32,200 --> 00:00:33,500
- You, too!
- Please don't hurt her.

12
00:00:33,600 --> 00:00:34,567
You, traitor!

13
00:00:34,633 --> 00:00:36,933
You're now jobless
because of what you did!

14
00:00:37,000 --> 00:00:38,567
You're fired!

15
00:00:38,633 --> 00:00:40,500
I did everything for you!

16
00:00:40,567 --> 00:00:42,167
And now you're talking back
to me?

17
00:00:42,233 --> 00:00:44,000
You're ungrateful!

18
00:00:44,067 --> 00:00:45,533
You always think
I don't care.

19
00:00:45,600 --> 00:00:48,900
You always say
I'm not concerned.

20
00:00:48,967 --> 00:00:50,933
She's not in any way
related to you.

21
00:00:51,000 --> 00:00:52,667
She's not your daughter,
but you care for her.

22
00:00:52,733 --> 00:00:53,533
How much more do you
think I care for you?

23
00:00:53,600 --> 00:00:55,167
You're my child.
I'm your mother.

24
00:01:34,500 --> 00:01:35,167
Emma.

25
00:01:45,100 --> 00:01:45,867
Dan.

26
00:01:46,900 --> 00:01:48,200
It's my fault.

27
00:01:49,467 --> 00:01:51,367
I was careless.

28
00:01:52,600 --> 00:01:54,267
I'm sure, Ma'am Olive

29
00:01:54,333 --> 00:01:56,933
is already punishing Mookie
right now.

30
00:01:57,000 --> 00:01:57,867
Emma, Emma.

31
00:01:59,533 --> 00:02:01,667
She'll eventually calm down.

32
00:02:02,900 --> 00:02:08,067
I'm sure she won't hurt Mookie.

33
00:02:08,133 --> 00:02:10,833
You don't know Ma'am Olive.

34
00:02:10,900 --> 00:02:12,733
I saw how angry she could get

35
00:02:12,800 --> 00:02:16,400
even though I was only there
for a while.

36
00:02:16,500 --> 00:02:19,933
Maybe it's better if you
don't come back there.

37
00:02:21,533 --> 00:02:22,633
It's dangerous.

38
00:02:22,700 --> 00:02:24,833
She might report you.

39
00:02:24,900 --> 00:02:27,067
And because she hates
you so much,

40
00:02:27,133 --> 00:02:30,100
she might take her anger
out on Mookie.

41
00:02:30,167 --> 00:02:33,100
I'm not sure if I can be
separated from Mookie.

42
00:02:33,167 --> 00:02:34,200
I don't want to.

43
00:02:34,267 --> 00:02:39,333
Ems, you might only cause
trouble in their family.

44
00:02:40,367 --> 00:02:42,433
I feel bad for the kid.

45
00:02:43,267 --> 00:02:47,433
Just think of
what's best for her.

46
00:02:49,200 --> 00:02:53,767
If you really care for Mookie,
you will leave them be.

47
00:03:48,667 --> 00:03:49,900
Forget about that.

48
00:03:53,300 --> 00:03:55,633
I bought you
something better.

49
00:04:01,133 --> 00:04:01,700
This.

50
00:04:20,033 --> 00:04:21,633
You know what, dear?

51
00:04:24,867 --> 00:04:27,133
I don't want to hurt you.

52
00:04:31,167 --> 00:04:32,567
But sometimes...

53
00:04:34,567 --> 00:04:35,800
I feel like...

54
00:04:37,000 --> 00:04:38,867
I no longer have a choice.

55
00:04:43,767 --> 00:04:45,600
Why is it wrong...

56
00:04:47,133 --> 00:04:49,333
to talk to Emma?

57
00:04:52,133 --> 00:04:55,233
How many times should
I remind you

58
00:04:56,533 --> 00:04:59,167
that your immune system
is fragile?

59
00:05:01,033 --> 00:05:05,267
You catch illnesses quickly.

60
00:05:07,033 --> 00:05:08,600
But, Mommy, I feel better now.

61
00:05:08,667 --> 00:05:09,400
No!

62
00:05:10,733 --> 00:05:13,100
You can get infected by anyone.

63
00:05:14,367 --> 00:05:15,500
Even by Emma.

64
00:05:16,800 --> 00:05:17,633
Who knows?

65
00:05:17,700 --> 00:05:20,100
Maybe she has an
infectious disease.

66
00:05:21,433 --> 00:05:22,467
Mommy, please.

67
00:05:23,600 --> 00:05:27,267
Please, let Emma
return to her job.

68
00:05:29,400 --> 00:05:35,600
I feel bad for her and her
family if she loses her job.

69
00:05:36,733 --> 00:05:37,900
Mookie...

70
00:05:40,000 --> 00:05:41,000
please.

71
00:05:43,400 --> 00:05:48,533
Don't give me a reason
to get mad at you again.

72
00:05:50,567 --> 00:05:51,533
Mommy, please.

73
00:05:52,233 --> 00:05:55,067
Promise I won't
talk to Emma again.

74
00:05:55,133 --> 00:05:56,433
I won't get near her.

75
00:05:56,500 --> 00:05:57,533
I will avoid her.

76
00:05:57,600 --> 00:05:59,133
I will do everything.

77
00:06:00,500 --> 00:06:03,167
Just let her
return to her job.

78
00:06:03,533 --> 00:06:04,633
Promise, Mommy.

79
00:06:06,100 --> 00:06:07,733
Who matters to you more?

80
00:06:10,467 --> 00:06:11,267
Me...

81
00:06:12,600 --> 00:06:14,033
or Emma?

82
00:06:17,233 --> 00:06:18,100
You.

83
00:06:18,600 --> 00:06:19,967
All right.

84
00:06:23,567 --> 00:06:25,567
So, do what I want.

85
00:06:27,400 --> 00:06:31,500
We had a peaceful life
before Emma came.

86
00:06:34,300 --> 00:06:38,833
She's just ruining our lives.

87
00:06:47,233 --> 00:06:48,500
Stop crying.

88
00:07:06,633 --> 00:07:08,267
I hope Mookie's okay.

89
00:07:09,433 --> 00:07:11,800
I hope I can see her
even for a bit.

90
00:07:33,933 --> 00:07:34,667
Emma?

91
00:07:40,933 --> 00:07:42,167
What are you doing here?

92
00:07:43,400 --> 00:07:47,767
I want to know how Mookie
is after the arcade incident.

93
00:07:48,400 --> 00:07:50,167
How is she doing?

94
00:07:51,167 --> 00:07:52,333
I don't know.

95
00:07:54,600 --> 00:07:56,767
I no longer work here.

96
00:07:56,833 --> 00:07:58,300
Her mom fired me.

97
00:07:59,033 --> 00:08:00,033
Is that so?

98
00:08:01,167 --> 00:08:02,167
Too bad.

99
00:08:02,867 --> 00:08:04,800
Mookie likes you so much.

100
00:08:05,667 --> 00:08:07,000
You have a different
kind of bond.

101
00:08:09,900 --> 00:08:11,767
Even if I'm not with her,

102
00:08:13,133 --> 00:08:19,467
I'll be okay as long
as she's safe and happy.

103
00:08:24,833 --> 00:08:26,900
I'll go ahead, Emma.

104
00:08:27,567 --> 00:08:28,567
Good night.

105
00:08:40,667 --> 00:08:43,500
Why don't you two talk?

106
00:08:44,200 --> 00:08:46,233
Yes, it's hard
to bottle it in.

107
00:08:46,300 --> 00:08:47,767
It might explode anytime.

108
00:08:51,533 --> 00:08:52,833
Look at Emma.

109
00:08:53,933 --> 00:08:55,867
She behaves like she
is Mookie's mother

110
00:08:55,967 --> 00:08:57,133
more than the kid's mom.

111
00:08:57,200 --> 00:09:01,767
You know Olive might come out
again.

112
00:09:02,600 --> 00:09:03,967
I don't understand her.

113
00:09:04,567 --> 00:09:06,200
She's so stubborn.

114
00:09:06,767 --> 00:09:08,700
Her head is harder
than a nutshell.

115
00:09:09,800 --> 00:09:10,800
She can do
whatever she wants.

116
00:09:11,333 --> 00:09:14,500
She'll be dead meat if
Olive sees her again.

117
00:09:16,333 --> 00:09:17,033
Oh, boy.

118
00:09:17,100 --> 00:09:18,100
Let's just go back.

119
00:09:18,167 --> 00:09:21,133
I might become
unlucky if I go home.

120
00:09:21,833 --> 00:09:22,533
Let's make a bet.

121
00:09:22,600 --> 00:09:24,133
I bet Olive
will come out.

122
00:09:24,200 --> 00:09:25,367
Are you sure?

123
00:09:25,433 --> 00:09:27,033
Yes, how much do you want?
100 pesos? 200 pesos? What?

124
00:09:27,100 --> 00:09:28,000
I bet for 300 pesos.

125
00:09:28,100 --> 00:09:29,267
Make it higher.

126
00:09:29,333 --> 00:09:30,200
Hey!
Let's go.

127
00:09:31,100 --> 00:09:32,533
We're coming.

128
00:09:34,267 --> 00:09:34,933
It's your fault.

129
00:09:46,633 --> 00:09:47,567
Mookie.

130
00:09:47,633 --> 00:09:49,633
Let's go upstairs.

131
00:09:49,700 --> 00:09:52,000
So I can close the door.

132
00:09:52,567 --> 00:09:53,067
Let's go.

133
00:09:54,000 --> 00:09:55,000
Flor.

134
00:09:57,067 --> 00:10:04,467
Give me a minute, please.

135
00:10:04,567 --> 00:10:05,633
Four house, six.

136
00:10:05,700 --> 00:10:07,167
I won!

137
00:10:11,233 --> 00:10:13,567
You lost again, Ligaya.

138
00:10:14,267 --> 00:10:16,300
Has your luck already left you?

139
00:10:17,133 --> 00:10:18,767
This is Olive's fault.

140
00:10:19,300 --> 00:10:20,967
Why?

141
00:10:21,033 --> 00:10:22,867
She's a witch.

142
00:10:22,933 --> 00:10:24,700
I can't take her off my mind.

143
00:10:26,200 --> 00:10:27,000
What do you mean?

144
00:10:27,067 --> 00:10:29,100
Are you in love
with Ma'am Olive?

145
00:10:29,167 --> 00:10:29,967
Silly!

146
00:10:31,100 --> 00:10:33,767
She fired my daughter,
who did nothing wrong!

147
00:10:33,833 --> 00:10:36,600
So I will deal with that witch!

148
00:10:37,633 --> 00:10:38,733
Looks like a war is brewing.

149
00:10:38,800 --> 00:10:43,367
Let's make a bet on who
will win the fight.

150
00:10:43,433 --> 00:10:45,067
Don't stop me!

151
00:10:45,133 --> 00:10:46,000
Hey, Madam!

152
00:10:46,067 --> 00:10:47,133
Let's have a talk!

153
00:10:47,200 --> 00:10:48,633
Come on, Ligaya!

154
00:10:48,700 --> 00:10:49,800
Don't make the problem worse!

155
00:10:49,867 --> 00:10:51,800
- What problem are you saying?
- Get out of here!

156
00:10:51,867 --> 00:10:53,000
She started it!

157
00:10:53,067 --> 00:10:54,133
I'll deal with her.

158
00:10:54,200 --> 00:10:56,100
Get out of here!

159
00:10:56,967 --> 00:10:57,800
So brave!

160
00:10:58,867 --> 00:11:01,300
I'll all in for Ligaya!

161
00:11:01,367 --> 00:11:02,067
Look!

162
00:11:02,133 --> 00:11:03,900
She's biting!

163
00:11:03,967 --> 00:11:04,967
Nice!

164
00:11:05,033 --> 00:11:07,733
Is there anyone braver
than the monster?

165
00:11:07,800 --> 00:11:09,300
I bet on Ma'am Olive.

166
00:11:09,400 --> 00:11:10,633
You keep saying Olive.

167
00:11:10,700 --> 00:11:12,000
Do you like her?

168
00:11:12,467 --> 00:11:13,233
Of course not.

169
00:11:13,300 --> 00:11:14,667
Look, look. She's coming.

170
00:11:14,733 --> 00:11:15,633
I don't fight with elderly.
Flor.

171
00:11:17,800 --> 00:11:18,667
Isn't it true?

172
00:11:18,733 --> 00:11:19,800
- Hey.
- Ma'am, she doesn't stop.

173
00:11:20,600 --> 00:11:22,067
- You again?
- You don't have manners!

174
00:11:23,167 --> 00:11:24,467
What are you doing here?

175
00:11:26,500 --> 00:11:27,767
We need to talk.

176
00:11:31,700 --> 00:11:32,600
Hello?
Emma!

177
00:11:34,133 --> 00:11:34,967
Emma!
Hello?

178
00:11:37,100 --> 00:11:38,200
Hello?

179
00:11:38,267 --> 00:11:40,800
I'm glad you're here, Emma!

180
00:11:40,900 --> 00:11:41,867
Your mom.

181
00:11:41,933 --> 00:11:43,767
Why?

182
00:11:43,833 --> 00:11:46,033
I'm going to collect a payment.

183
00:11:46,100 --> 00:11:47,500
Have you lost your mind?

184
00:11:48,433 --> 00:11:50,800
How did I become
indebted to you?

185
00:11:50,867 --> 00:11:53,367
Madam, I took care of you
at the hospital.

186
00:11:53,433 --> 00:11:54,567
I watch over you.

187
00:11:54,633 --> 00:11:57,500
Is the money I gave you
still not enough?

188
00:11:57,567 --> 00:12:03,500
What you gave me was a payment
for losing in the card game.

189
00:12:03,567 --> 00:12:08,167
But I don't want money in
return for taking care of you.

190
00:12:10,033 --> 00:12:14,100
Please, don't
waste my time.

191
00:12:14,200 --> 00:12:15,500
Just get to the point.

192
00:12:16,100 --> 00:12:19,333
I want you to
forgive Emma.

193
00:12:19,967 --> 00:12:20,900
What?

194
00:12:21,667 --> 00:12:23,933
Let her return to her job.

195
00:12:24,000 --> 00:12:25,167
Accept her again!

196
00:12:29,233 --> 00:12:30,067
Here.

197
00:12:30,900 --> 00:12:32,267
I'm begging you.

198
00:12:34,900 --> 00:12:35,667
Oh.
What happened?

199
00:12:37,133 --> 00:12:38,267
Will you please get up!

200
00:12:38,333 --> 00:12:41,533
- I won't get up here.
- Kneeling won't work for me.

201
00:12:41,600 --> 00:12:44,067
I won't move until you
accept Emma again.

202
00:12:45,233 --> 00:12:48,100
She's even begging.

203
00:12:49,267 --> 00:12:51,500
Madam, I'm begging you.

204
00:12:52,833 --> 00:12:54,867
You don't understand Emma.

205
00:12:56,033 --> 00:12:58,233
Emma lost a child.

206
00:12:58,300 --> 00:13:01,200
Her daughter would've been
the same age as Mookie

207
00:13:01,267 --> 00:13:03,533
if she had been alive.

208
00:13:03,600 --> 00:13:05,633
She only longs for her child.

209
00:13:05,700 --> 00:13:07,567
That's why she gets
near your daughter.

210
00:13:08,733 --> 00:13:10,333
I don't care.

211
00:13:11,333 --> 00:13:13,433
Your daughter is stubborn.

212
00:13:14,333 --> 00:13:15,433
Mom, let's go.

213
00:13:15,500 --> 00:13:16,433
Get up.

214
00:13:16,500 --> 00:13:17,767
Leave me be!

215
00:13:17,833 --> 00:13:19,367
She's telling the truth.

216
00:13:19,433 --> 00:13:20,733
You really are stubborn.

217
00:13:20,800 --> 00:13:22,667
You keep
approaching the kid.

218
00:13:24,133 --> 00:13:27,600
Madam, let's talk it over.

219
00:13:27,667 --> 00:13:28,633
Please.

220
00:13:29,467 --> 00:13:34,633
We'll suffer if Emma
loses her job.

221
00:13:34,700 --> 00:13:36,133
It's no longer my problem.

222
00:13:37,233 --> 00:13:41,267
Get out of here, and
don't ever come back.

223
00:13:41,567 --> 00:13:43,233
- I'm begging you...
- Flor.

224
00:13:43,867 --> 00:13:45,900
Flor, make them leave.

225
00:13:45,967 --> 00:13:47,367
- Mom.
- Please, I'm begging you.

226
00:13:47,433 --> 00:13:49,367
- Hey, let go of me!
- Madam!

227
00:13:49,433 --> 00:13:51,233
I said let go of me!

228
00:13:51,300 --> 00:13:52,300
What are you doing?

229
00:13:55,433 --> 00:13:56,300
Hey!

230
00:14:00,633 --> 00:14:02,667
I'm begging you.

231
00:14:05,533 --> 00:14:08,033
I don't have a job.

232
00:14:08,100 --> 00:14:12,600
I only depend on Emma
and her husband.

233
00:14:12,667 --> 00:14:13,800
Look at me.

234
00:14:13,867 --> 00:14:15,667
I'm already old.

235
00:14:15,733 --> 00:14:17,133
I'm weak.

236
00:14:17,200 --> 00:14:19,200
When I get sick,

237
00:14:19,267 --> 00:14:23,500
we don't know where to get money
for my medication.

238
00:14:23,567 --> 00:14:25,333
So, please.

239
00:14:25,400 --> 00:14:29,400
I'm begging you.

240
00:14:29,500 --> 00:14:31,000
Please forgive Emma.

241
00:14:31,067 --> 00:14:32,867
Please, Madam.

242
00:14:33,333 --> 00:14:34,400
Madam.

243
00:14:34,867 --> 00:14:35,800
I'm begging you.

244
00:14:37,833 --> 00:14:39,533
Please.

245
00:14:39,600 --> 00:14:40,800
I'm begging you.

246
00:14:40,867 --> 00:14:42,600
Please forgive Emma.

247
00:14:42,667 --> 00:14:44,600
Please, Madam.

248
00:14:44,667 --> 00:14:45,833
Madam.

249
00:14:45,900 --> 00:14:47,433
I'm begging you.

250
00:14:49,133 --> 00:14:50,433
Okay, okay!

251
00:14:50,500 --> 00:14:51,300
Fine!
Yes!

252
00:14:57,800 --> 00:14:59,600
Are you going to
hire Emma again?

253
00:15:00,433 --> 00:15:01,567
Yes!

254
00:15:02,967 --> 00:15:05,167
I can now return
to my job, Ma'am?

255
00:15:06,533 --> 00:15:09,967
Madam, you're God sent.

256
00:15:11,767 --> 00:15:12,600
Please!

257
00:15:12,967 --> 00:15:14,200
- Mom.
- Let me go!

258
00:15:15,733 --> 00:15:17,200
Don't touch me!

259
00:15:20,300 --> 00:15:21,367
Go ahead, Flor!

260
00:15:22,767 --> 00:15:24,100
Make them leave!

261
00:15:24,167 --> 00:15:25,033
Yes, Ma'am.

262
00:15:27,667 --> 00:15:29,233
Go. Come back tomorrow.

263
00:15:33,700 --> 00:15:34,367
- Go. Leave.
- Emma, let me carry that.

264
00:15:34,433 --> 00:15:36,000
You heard Madam, didn't you?

265
00:15:36,633 --> 00:15:38,800
You even spread the
dirt that I swept.

266
00:15:39,533 --> 00:15:40,867
Go, Emma. Take your mom with
you.

267
00:15:41,433 --> 00:15:42,567
Let's go.

268
00:15:43,533 --> 00:15:45,767
- Let's go.
- What happened to you?

269
00:15:45,833 --> 00:15:47,933
- Oh my God.
- Go. Leave.

270
00:15:48,000 --> 00:15:50,167
Why did you fold?

271
00:15:50,867 --> 00:15:52,700
I lost a lot
to you, Kutsy.

272
00:15:53,533 --> 00:15:55,200
It's your fault.

273
00:15:55,267 --> 00:15:56,967
I thought you were brave.

274
00:15:57,033 --> 00:15:58,867
You said you were brave.

275
00:15:59,833 --> 00:16:01,267
But you're not.

276
00:16:02,400 --> 00:16:03,767
Hey, Wiro!

277
00:16:03,833 --> 00:16:04,667
Come back here!

278
00:16:04,733 --> 00:16:05,700
No!

279
00:16:05,767 --> 00:16:07,033
You still owe me a hundred.

280
00:16:07,100 --> 00:16:08,533
- No, none!
- Oh, boy.

281
00:16:11,000 --> 00:16:11,767
Mom.

282
00:16:13,000 --> 00:16:15,600
I know you're after my salary.

283
00:16:15,667 --> 00:16:16,433
But...

284
00:16:17,133 --> 00:16:19,667
you shouldn't
stoop that low.

285
00:16:21,000 --> 00:16:23,400
What matters is
that it worked.

286
00:16:24,200 --> 00:16:26,533
I did that not
only for money.

287
00:16:27,200 --> 00:16:28,867
Of course, for the salary.

288
00:16:28,933 --> 00:16:32,800
So we can pay our rent.
Right, Mom?

289
00:16:33,467 --> 00:16:34,600
You're so mean.

290
00:16:35,667 --> 00:16:38,133
That's what only
matters to you, right?

291
00:16:40,300 --> 00:16:41,400
Whatever.

292
00:16:43,033 --> 00:16:45,233
Think whatever you like.

293
00:16:45,300 --> 00:16:48,233
Will you believe me if I tell
you I want you to be happy?

294
00:16:48,300 --> 00:16:49,500
Of course, you won't.

295
00:16:49,567 --> 00:16:51,667
Because you see me as
a worthless person.

296
00:16:56,400 --> 00:16:57,100
Mom.
Mom.

297
00:17:00,000 --> 00:17:00,767
You know what?

298
00:17:01,600 --> 00:17:03,367
You're right.

299
00:17:03,433 --> 00:17:06,633
People get comfortable
with you easily.

300
00:17:07,333 --> 00:17:08,533
Look.

301
00:17:08,600 --> 00:17:12,033
You found a job for me, to work
for Ma'am Olive.

302
00:17:12,100 --> 00:17:16,667
And you even fixed the problem
so I could return to my job.

303
00:17:17,933 --> 00:17:18,967
Thank you, Mom.

304
00:17:40,933 --> 00:17:41,867
Ma'am.

305
00:17:42,900 --> 00:17:46,767
I'm glad you let Emma
return to her job.

306
00:17:46,833 --> 00:17:49,400
If not, I will break my back

307
00:17:49,500 --> 00:17:51,200
from all the laundry
I must finish.

308
00:17:52,400 --> 00:17:55,667
It's not easy to hire a
laundress these days.

309
00:17:57,067 --> 00:17:58,300
Really?

310
00:17:58,367 --> 00:18:00,067
Is that the only reason?

311
00:18:00,133 --> 00:18:02,633
Or do you feel
sorry for Ligaya?

312
00:18:06,500 --> 00:18:08,633
Shut up.

313
00:18:10,067 --> 00:18:12,300
You like Ligaya,
don't you?

314
00:18:14,233 --> 00:18:18,200
If you don't stop,
I will fire you.

315
00:18:19,267 --> 00:18:19,967
Okay.

316
00:18:20,033 --> 00:18:21,567
I will stop now.

317
00:18:22,033 --> 00:18:22,833
Bye, Ma'am.

318
00:18:27,967 --> 00:18:29,133
We're not close.

319
00:18:30,267 --> 00:18:33,367
And do you think I'm not
aware of what you're doing?

320
00:18:33,933 --> 00:18:35,433
You only want to
extort money from me.

321
00:18:36,033 --> 00:18:36,733
What?

322
00:18:36,800 --> 00:18:37,833
I'm not dumb.

323
00:18:38,467 --> 00:18:39,767
Of course not!

324
00:18:39,833 --> 00:18:42,067
I really want to
take care of you.

325
00:18:42,133 --> 00:18:43,100
Fine.

326
00:18:43,167 --> 00:18:46,900
We're just a little close

327
00:18:46,967 --> 00:18:50,333
if you can't accept that
we are close friends.

328
00:18:59,633 --> 00:19:00,733
Where are you going?

329
00:19:01,500 --> 00:19:02,800
I'll assist you.

330
00:19:03,700 --> 00:19:06,400
You might get
dizzy and fall.

331
00:19:06,467 --> 00:19:08,100
I'll catch you.

332
00:19:08,167 --> 00:19:09,000
Let's go.

333
00:19:10,900 --> 00:19:11,700
It's okay.

334
00:19:12,300 --> 00:19:13,233
I can do this.

335
00:19:14,000 --> 00:19:14,767
Thank you.

336
00:19:25,967 --> 00:19:27,733
I wonder how Mookie is doing.

337
00:19:28,700 --> 00:19:30,733
I wasn't able to talk
to her last night.

338
00:19:33,600 --> 00:19:34,933
How is she?

339
00:19:35,000 --> 00:19:39,800
I'm glad Mom convinced
Ma'am Olive to return to work.

340
00:19:39,867 --> 00:19:44,533
Because I miss Mookie so much.

341
00:19:45,633 --> 00:19:49,400
She's the reason why I
don't miss Kayla anymore.

342
00:20:12,467 --> 00:20:13,267
Danilo.

343
00:20:13,933 --> 00:20:15,367
Danilo, look.

344
00:20:15,433 --> 00:20:17,533
They have the same lips.

345
00:20:20,633 --> 00:20:22,033
You're at it again, Ems.

346
00:20:22,867 --> 00:20:26,567
I wonder what Mookie looked like
when she was little.

347
00:20:26,967 --> 00:20:29,933
And was she already
sick at that time?

348
00:20:30,667 --> 00:20:33,467
Don't you see any pictures
of her in their house?

349
00:20:34,467 --> 00:20:36,367
Childhood pictures.

350
00:20:38,533 --> 00:20:39,600
There's nothing.

351
00:20:40,033 --> 00:20:40,933
Nothing?

352
00:20:41,000 --> 00:20:42,367
I wonder why.

353
00:20:50,700 --> 00:20:52,633
Madam, thank you so...

354
00:20:55,600 --> 00:20:56,767
Thank you.

355
00:20:57,167 --> 00:21:04,133
I know and believe you have
kindness in your heart, Madam.

356
00:21:05,467 --> 00:21:07,567
It's not easy to
find a laundress.

357
00:21:08,667 --> 00:21:11,500
Thank you still.

358
00:21:14,833 --> 00:21:18,500
Ma'am Olive, thank
you for this job.

359
00:21:18,567 --> 00:21:20,767
This means a lot
to our family.

360
00:21:21,833 --> 00:21:23,767
I'm warning you, Emma.

361
00:21:24,867 --> 00:21:27,733
Stay the hell away
from my daughter.

362
00:21:27,800 --> 00:21:29,533
Don't worry, Madam.

363
00:21:30,633 --> 00:21:33,000
Emma has learned her lesson.

364
00:21:33,067 --> 00:21:37,400
She won't do anything
that will make you mad.

365
00:21:37,467 --> 00:21:38,967
Right?

366
00:21:39,033 --> 00:21:39,600
Yes.

367
00:21:42,100 --> 00:21:43,433
Make sure of that.

368
00:21:43,967 --> 00:21:46,667
Because you don't know
what I'm capable of.

369
00:21:47,467 --> 00:21:52,300
If you do that again,
I won't just fire you.

370
00:21:52,367 --> 00:21:56,833
I will find a way to kick
you out of your house

371
00:21:56,900 --> 00:21:58,467
and out of this place.

372
00:22:01,133 --> 00:22:02,500
Do you understand?

373
00:22:10,000 --> 00:22:11,133
Mommy Emma.

374
00:22:13,800 --> 00:22:15,700
Mommy Emma is back.

375
00:22:21,667 --> 00:22:22,600
There.

376
00:22:23,133 --> 00:22:23,767
Thank you, Flor.
Are you okay?

377
00:22:25,500 --> 00:22:27,133
Is it true?

378
00:22:27,800 --> 00:22:30,167
My mom let me go downstairs?

379
00:22:30,233 --> 00:22:33,000
You keep asking me that.

380
00:22:33,067 --> 00:22:35,200
I've already said yes.

381
00:22:35,267 --> 00:22:36,867
Why can't you believe it?

382
00:22:36,933 --> 00:22:37,967
That's Mookie.

383
00:22:48,867 --> 00:22:51,133
Just always behave.

384
00:22:51,200 --> 00:22:52,133
Be a good girl.
Okay?

385
00:22:54,633 --> 00:22:55,800
Stay here.

386
00:22:55,867 --> 00:22:57,200
I'll get you snacks.

387
00:22:57,867 --> 00:22:58,933
Okay, Flor.

388
00:22:59,000 --> 00:22:59,700
All right.

389
00:23:07,500 --> 00:23:08,567
Why, Ma'am?

390
00:23:08,633 --> 00:23:09,700
What's going on?

391
00:23:10,667 --> 00:23:12,633
What's your plan?

392
00:23:14,900 --> 00:23:20,000
I want to know if Emma
will keep her word.

393
00:24:00,167 --> 00:24:01,967
This is me?

394
00:24:03,000 --> 00:24:04,567
Yes, Mookie. It's you.

395
00:24:04,633 --> 00:24:09,000
I saw it in your mom's office
when Flor and I cleaned.

396
00:24:09,067 --> 00:24:09,900
Look.

397
00:24:09,967 --> 00:24:11,233
You look so healthy.

398
00:24:12,033 --> 00:24:13,367
You don't seem to be sick.

399
00:24:13,433 --> 00:24:15,267
You still get near Mookie?

400
00:24:15,333 --> 00:24:18,900
And you act as if you're
the kid's mother.

401
00:24:18,967 --> 00:24:20,467
Mookie!

402
00:24:20,900 --> 00:24:21,367
Virgie!

403
00:24:21,433 --> 00:24:22,400
Ligaya?

404
00:24:22,467 --> 00:24:24,167
What are you doing here?

405
00:24:24,233 --> 00:24:26,167
Ever since I lost them,

406
00:24:26,233 --> 00:24:28,700
it feels like something in me
is missing.

407
00:24:29,133 --> 00:24:30,467
My being a mother.

408
00:24:30,533 --> 00:24:32,033
I don't feel complete.

409
00:24:32,100 --> 00:24:35,367
Who told you to
take this picture?

410
00:24:35,433 --> 00:24:37,667
Who told you to keep it?

411
00:24:37,733 --> 00:24:38,733
Who told you?

412
00:24:38,800 --> 00:24:40,167
Answer me!

413
00:24:40,233 --> 00:24:41,933
Mommy, why are you getting mad?

414
00:24:42,000 --> 00:24:43,933
It's just a picture.

415
00:24:44,000 --> 00:24:45,533
Shut up!

416
00:24:45,600 --> 00:24:48,400
Is it because I look healthy
in that picture, Mommy?

417
00:24:49,533 --> 00:24:51,433
Is it because I'm not sick?

418
00:24:51,500 --> 00:24:53,133
You don't believe me?

419
00:24:53,200 --> 00:24:55,000
You're sick!

420
00:24:55,067 --> 00:24:56,167
Accept that you're sick.

421
00:24:56,233 --> 00:24:57,733
And you will never get better!
